Question 1: How does the presence of one or more highly popular songs in an album affect the popularity and listener engagement of other tracks within the same album?

In[2]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.stats import ttest_ind
#pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)

data = pd.read_csv("./data/dataset.csv")
data = data.drop(columns='Unnamed: 0')
data = data.drop_duplicates(subset=['album_name', 'track_name'])

# How does the presence of one or more highly popular songs in an album affect the 
# popularity and listener engagement of other tracks within the same album?

data_copy = data.copy()
data_copy['popular'] = 'null'
data_copy['popular'] = data_copy['popularity'].apply(lambda x: 'Yes' if x > 50 else 'No')

averaged_data = data_copy.groupby(['album_name'])['popularity'].mean().reset_index()

popular_songs = data_copy[data_copy['popular'] == 'Yes']
lister = list(set(popular_songs['album_name']))

popular_albums = data_copy[data_copy['album_name'].isin(lister)]
unpopular_albums = data_copy[~data_copy['album_name'].isin(lister)]

popular_albums_avg = popular_albums.groupby(['album_name'])['popularity'].mean().reset_index()

averaged_data['group'] = averaged_data['album_name'].apply(lambda x: 'Popular' if x in lister else 'Unpopular')


plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.histplot(data=averaged_data, x='popularity', hue='group', bins=50, palette='muted')
plt.title('Distribution of Album Popularity by Presence of Highly Popular Songs')
plt.xlabel('Average Album Popularity')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.legend(title='Album Type', labels=['Popular', 'Unpopular'])
plt.show()

total_popular = data_copy[data_copy['album_name'].isin(popular_albums['album_name'])]
popular_album_no_song = total_popular[~total_popular['track_name'].isin(popular_songs['track_name'])]
popular_album_no_song = popular_album_no_song.groupby(['album_name'])['popularity'].mean().reset_index()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.histplot(data=popular_album_no_song, x='popularity')
plt.title('Average popularity of albums after removing the popular songs')
plt.xlabel('Average Album Popularity')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.show()


numerical_columns = [
    'popularity', 'duration_ms', 'danceability', 'energy', 'key', 
    'loudness', 'mode', 'speechiness', 'acousticness', 
    'instrumentalness', 'liveness', 'valence', 'tempo', 'time_signature'
]
numerical_data = data_copy[numerical_columns]
correlation_matrix = numerical_data.corr()

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', fmt=".2f", linewidths=0.5)
plt.title("Heatmap of Attribute Correlations")
plt.show()

# Group by album_name and calculate total songs and popular songs
album_song_counts = total_popular.groupby('album_name').agg(total_songs=('track_id', 'count'), popular_songs=('popularity', lambda x: (x > 50).sum())).reset_index()
album_song_counts['percent_popular'] = (album_song_counts['popular_songs'] / album_song_counts['total_songs']) * 100
album_song_counts.sort_values(by='percent_popular', ascending=False, inplace=True)
more_than_one = album_song_counts[album_song_counts['total_songs']>1]


plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.histplot(data=more_than_one, x='percent_popular')
plt.title('Percentage of popular songs in an album (More than 1 track)')
plt.xlabel('Percentage')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.show()

def is_collaboration(artists):
    return ';' in artists  

df['is_collaboration'] = df['artists'].apply(lambda x: is_collaboration(x) if pd.notnull(x) else False)

musical_attributes = [

    'speechiness', 'acousticness', 'instrumentalness', 'liveness', 'valence', 'tempo', 
    'time_signature'
]

fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(musical_attributes), 1, figsize=(10, 4 * len(musical_attributes)))

for i, attribute in enumerate(musical_attributes):
    sns.histplot(df[df['is_collaboration'] == True][attribute], color='blue', label='Collaboration', kde=False, bins=30, ax=axes[i])
    sns.histplot(df[df['is_collaboration'] == False][attribute], color='orange', label='Solo', kde=False, bins=30, ax=axes[i])
    axes[i].set_title(f'Distribution of {attribute} for Solo vs Collaboration Tracks')
    axes[i].set_xlabel(attribute)
    axes[i].set_ylabel('Frequency')
    axes[i].legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
from tabulate import tabulate

artist_popularity = df.groupby('artists')['popularity'].sum().reset_index()
artist_popularity.columns = ['artists', 'total_popularity']

max_popularity = artist_popularity['total_popularity'].max()
artist_popularity['normalized_popularity'] = (artist_popularity['total_popularity'] / max_popularity) * 100

artist_popularity_sorted = artist_popularity.sort_values(by='normalized_popularity', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)

top_10_artists_popularity = artist_popularity_sorted.head(10)

top_10_artists_popularity.insert(0, "Rank", range(1, len(top_10_artists_popularity) + 1))

top_10_artists_popularity = top_10_artists_popularity[['Rank', 'artists', 'normalized_popularity']]

table = tabulate(
    top_10_artists_popularity,
    headers=top_10_artists_popularity.columns,
    tablefmt="pretty"
)

print(table)
